    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your casserole dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Note: Make sure your dish is oven-proof and safe to use on the hob. Don't have one? Start cooking in a large, wide-based pan then transfer to an oven-proof dish and cover tightly with foil</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-butter-chicken-tortiglioni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based <strong>hob-safe</strong> <strong>oven-proof casserole dish </strong>with a matching lid with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced chicken breast </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>and cook for 3 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-butter-chicken-tortiglioni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice your<strong> shallot[s]</strong> finely</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-butter-chicken-tortiglioni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken is starting to brown, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>curry powder</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>and<strong> </strong>1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong></p><p>Cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-butter-chicken-tortiglioni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>tortiglioni</strong> to the dish with a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[750ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Nestle the <strong>tortiglioni</strong> into the water as much as you can, then stir everything together and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-butter-chicken-tortiglioni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until the pasta is cooked and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Tip: Give everything a stir halfway through for evenly cooked pasta!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-butter-chicken-tortiglioni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once cooked, remove the dish from the oven and add the<strong> spinach</strong>,<strong> clotted cream</strong>, <strong>garam masala </strong>and<strong> </strong>a very generous<strong> </strong>knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Gently stir<strong> </strong>until the spinach starts to wilt \u2013 this is your <strong>one pot butter chicken tortiglioni</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-butter-chicken-tortiglioni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>one pot butter chicken tortiglioni </strong>and garnish with a good crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
